        <div class="msgSubject">Please stop letting RMT people ruin our games</div>
        <div class="sm notbold">
          
          Posted: 2010-10-05 03:55:44   | <input type="checkbox" name="quote-12862725443480536" id="quote-12862725443480536" class="msgQuoteCheck" onchange="multiQuote2()"/><label for="quote-12862725443480536" onclick="multiQuote2()"> Quote</label>  | <a href="/forum.html?forum=173&amp;mid=12862725443480536&amp;post=1&amp;replyto=12862725443480536&amp;page=1" class="icon-replytothis" rel="nofollow">Reply to Post</a> | <a id="FOLLOW_MID_12862725443480536" onclick="followToggle('add','12862725443480536')" href="javascript:" class="icon-follow">Follow</a> 
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="msgWhoFrame">
        <div class="msgUM"><a class="msgWhoName " href="/users/Dreamingness">Dreamingness</a></div><div class="msgAvatar"></div><div class="msgStar"></div><div class="msgWhoNum">5 posts</div>
        <div class="msgScore">
          Score: Excellent  
          <div class="msgRatings"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="msgContentFrame">I've been playing MMOs for some time. In that time I've seen a marked increase in additional game mechanics and restrictions all centered around the idea of making it difficult for RMT people to ruin these games.  <br /> <br />It's not working.  <br /> <br />I'm sure a lot of you are now saying to yourselves &quot;What? I see no gold seller people in FFXIV, what's this guy talking about?&quot; I don't know about you all, but I can see gold sellers in all games, whether they are spamming or not.  <br /> <br />Everytime I need to find something specific for sale and there's no auction house &quot;because we don't want RMT to ruin the economy&quot;, I see gold sellers. <br /> <br />I see them everytime I want to pay for another retainer in FFXIV and cannot. <br /> <br />Whenever I type some fragment of a word they use all the time, and the chat filter engages causing me to have to retype the message a different way, they appear like unwanted pests. <br /> <br />Each time I see a limit on gold transaction amounts or trades, there they are.  <br /> <br />There's one possibly hiding everytime I want to sort my inventory and cannot.  <br /> <br />If I were an alien race, I would be eating the equivalent of popcorn watching our planet merely for the entertainment value. We humans absolutely love to oppose something or some group of people...most always forgetting that by doing so, we give what we oppose even more power than it had when it started annoying us. You can find examples of this everywhere on our planet if you spend the effort to look. <br /> <br />Game mechanics that make it harder on the gold sellers typically wind up making it harder on the players. Please don't make us suffer for the transgressions of those people who value money above all else. Please allow us <i>some</i> comfort in playing the game we paid you for. Thank you for listening, if you are. </div>
