      <div class="msgContentFrame">It's easy to forget to mention the good things and exaggerate the bad.  <br /> <br />Yes, RMT will always be a problem in any online game where people are willing to pay money for game content. And considering that people shell out ****tons in crap like farmville, I'd say pretty much every official mmo is going to be a major market. <br /> <br />It's also true that various counter measures do sometimes interfere, or cheapen the gameplay for us players. Again, this holds true in all online games at this point, whether the countermeasures are obvious or subtle, they are indeed there and at work, and it does influence the way we play. <br /> <br />Now, here is the part many may forget... They are not all bad for the players... Did you play FFXI? Do you remember camping for an NM, and competing against RMT bots? Do you remember when it was so bad, there were inhumanly fast bots on every possible spawn point for every worthwhile NM? How about when you go mining, and there are bots sitting on every mining node spawn point? It was bull****, and if there have to be some countermeasures put in place, it's the lesser of two evils. Yes, the game might not be quite as fun with them, but it's still fun, as opposed to being no fun at all when it's overrun with bots. <br /> <br />It's a constant struggle to keep them from ruining the game at any given time. They even made earning gil 50x easier for the lazy and incompetent people, and there will still be no shortage of buyers. I agree that SE should ban buyers as well as sellers on sight. <br /> <br />And that tired old argument gil buyers use is a crock of ****. &quot;blah blah blah my time is precious I must buy gil I don't want to farm&quot;. Suck it up, if you don't play as much as the average player, it will take you longer to accomplish the same things as them. It's fine that way. Don't try to circumvent it, or I hope you do get banned. Just enjoy the game at whatever pace suits you, it's a game, not an epeen contest about who can get what first. People will still self justify their actions regardless of what they are though, so it really doesn't matter. <br /> <br />Overall I'm with SE's choice. They did a lot of good at launch to thwart bots, but they will have to keep up with it and use harsh ban waves to really get the point across to people. RMT will never be stamped out, but with enough effort, you can push them into the woodwork where they mostly keep out of the way. But even if they were completely banished from the game, they would still use the buy/sell method(buy gil for money, sell back for profit) which lets them sell gil without ever stepping foot in the game, beyond bank mules. <br /> <br />So yeah, that's my take on it... I personally just try to play around it all and not get involved, it's only when things get really out of hand, such as mass bot competition, that it ruffles my feathers.</div>
