      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Izuul wrote:</div><div class="orig">Do whatever Blizzard does because, aside from account theft which they can't control, RMT are virtually a non-factor in WoW.  I can't even think of one incident where my game play was in any way influenced by them in the two years that i played.</div></div>This is where we'd see a conflict in design philosophy. WoW is designed around a person being able to progress and level on their own because of how quests work. Consumables are what make the economy pretty much (well, aside from gear to disenchant). The thing is that most of the stuff for crafting is relatively easy to come by. I think the only things that were rare through this expansion were titanium ore (which was a base material for most high level crafted gear) and frost lotus (for flasks used during raids). <br /> <br />If FFXI was any indication, the devs have a certain amount of time they expect something to take, and in their minds, the longer the better. Blizzard is able to add content to the game because of how level progression and raid tiers work in WoW (hence why they didn't bother with making things like leveling crafts take months or years), which is something that wouldn't work in FFXIV or FFXI due to how the game was designed. <br /> <br />Lastly, Blizzard didn't focus much on item rarity, and the gear that was rare while leveling was not so ridiculously powerful that it could last you for most of your leveling career (leaping boots come to mind). <br /> <br />TLDR: Item value and gear value in WoW being low to moderate due to 90% of useful items not being stupidly rare is why RMT does not have much of a foothold in WoW. As much as I'd like SE's devs try their hand using that design philosophy, I don't see it happening anytime soon, if ever. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Oct 18th 2010  3:31am by Ruisu </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://yare-yare.com/beseiged.jpg" rel="external nofollow" title="yare-yare.com/beseiged.jpg">Beseiged</a> <br /><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Text-based WoW wrote:</div><div class="orig">&gt;West of House  <br />&gt;You are standing in an open field west of a white house, with a boarded front door.  <br />&gt;There is a small mailbox here.  <br />&gt;  <br />&gt;  <br />&gt;A Female Night Elf in her panties is dancing on the mailbox.  <br />&gt;▐</div></div></div></div>
