reinventing the wheel has failed and they need to start working on moving the game in a different direction.  <br /> <br />Crafting needs to be completely overhauled, the amount of materials for low level items and the need for high level crafters to make low level materials needs to be drastically altered. It's not fun, it's not going to keep me playing this game. The market ward system was a novel idea but it hasn't worked out, an Auction House is a time honored proven system and I think they need to just run with it.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Quote:</div><div class="orig">Pikko wrote: <br /><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Quote:</div><div class="orig"> sideways wrote: (really Pikko?)</div></div> <br />Oh go stuff that thread up your ass. Did you even READ that post? <br />[...] <br />I mean, excuuuuse me for trying to make people PLAY NICE.</div></div> <br /> <br />^ Second best forum mod smack down <b>*ever*</b>.</div></div>
