      <div class="msgContentFrame">Lets take a look at what SE has done (and failed) to try to curb RMT: <br /> <br /> <br />1- No Auction House. Why? To prevent the ease of RMT using a few accounts to utterly dominate a server's market as it happened in FF11. What the AH did was provide them with the means to undercut everyone else, constantly, to receive gil to sell for real money.  <br /> <br />Failure: RMT's have already set up multiple accounts to have multiple retainers and afk-sellbots stationed in all city wards and even in leve camps. There is no easy search option sure, but when a sell-bot/retainer is on the same spot on a permanent basis selling cheap it gets noticed and gets massive repeat business and word-of-mouth advertising. <br /> <br />2- Server side confirmation for everything in the game world before it is allowed to be executed. This was done to prevent botting and 3rd pty software programs (sniffer bots, scrying bots,etc).  <br /> <br />Failure: Massive interface lag in both transactions and combat. SE royally eff'd everyone by trying to limit the options of a few. It is pathetic to see that regardless of this, bots have already been seen in the game both harvesting, fishing and killing mobs for drops. <br /> <br />3- No auto-attack. Again, this was done to limit botting.  <br /> <br />Failure: Due to interface lag brought upon by server side confirmation of every damn action BEFORE it can be taken, the current combat system is extremely tiring to use plus it is very prone to failure as you tell your character to perform an action (attack or heal) and the game just doesnt do it because somewhere the packet for server confirmation just didnt go through.  <br /> <br />Failure X2: bots are easily programmed to perform attacks anyways so what was the point of this? <br /> <br />4- Huge amounts of gil pumped into economy through leves. This was perhaps to cause inflation on purpose and discourage RMT selling gil because this, coupled with the non-ah system (which causes prices of commodities to flux wildly), makes the worth of gil subjective.  <br /> <br />Failure: Regardless, Gil will be sold. RMT will simply adjust to the inflation level and just like players buy a rank 12 weapon for 200k where 2 bazaars down it was selling for 10k (they just didnt see it), RMT sites will keep selling gil at whatever price is profitable TO THEM.  <br /> <br />Failure 2: The economy is now not based on gil but rather crystals and shards. They are the only high demand, relatively rare (due to fast consumption of), relatively easy to get in bulk items. In many servers it has become standard to pay crafters for items in shards and crystals rather than gil itself. The result was quick to be seen: <br /> <br />RMT sellbot accounts are selling shards and crystals at undercut prices and their retainers are always stocked to the hilt with them. RMT sites even SELL shards and crystals (no other items.. only gil and shards/crystals).  <br /> <br />way to go SE.  <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Oct 31st 2010  1:16pm by Skyfaller </span></i></div>
