      <div class="msgContentFrame">@ cornyboob : <br />&quot;If SE just informs its players how to succeed and provide methods that dont involve this massive level of grinding then we can succeed on our own and RMT will die... &quot; <br /> <br />You're suggesting that instead of having to think about how we play, we're just given the answers instead? <br /> <br />I don't agree. <br /> <br />The reason why I like to occasionally re-sign with WoW is because of it's mindlessness. I know when I was playing FFXI, spotting in occasional bouts of WoW was like getting a 15 minute massage to FFXI's 5 day test match. The mindlessness, the easy drops, the rarely having to buy gear if at all because the mobs drop gear that's more than sufficient to get you by, the easy lvling exp via quests. I also played solo on WoW when I got sick and tired of ls politics in FFXI. <br /> <br />Conversely the difficulty, the need to plan, is exactly why I <u><b>adore</b></u> both FFXI and FFXIV. <br />When you finally accomplish a goal you've set yourself it actually feels like success, attainment, true reward for the hard yakka put in. So, no, I don't agree that we should just be told how to succeed. That would completely ruin the FF's for me. <br /> <br />Having said the above, it is the difficulty, the need to plan, etc which is precisely what encourages RMT in games and perhaps is why it is so prevalent in FFXI. This is alleviated somewhat by the fact that you <u>can get good gear drops </u> from completing levequests successfully in a (if only slightly) similar way to WoW drops. When it comes to gamer mentality - there are those who think games are like playing Snap, and if it's more difficult than Snap, well either they'll quit or they'll pay RMTs. Fools and their money..... Then there are players like me who *like* the challenge ... so long as it's reasonable. It has to be said some of the areas of FFXI were ridiculous. The memory of Promyvian-Dem still has the power to make me (run away!) ^^ <br />Coincidentally - the changes they have made to the gaming mechanics for FFXIV seem to address all the reasons why in the end I not only quit FFXI but uninstalled it and broke the discs as well. The emphasis on enabling solo gaming as a viable option, the recognition of crafting effort, the ability to adjust battle leves to suit the party make-up all these things are positives for me &amp; I am loving FFXIV so far. <br /> <br />I even like the idea of the retainer system. Sure an AH would be wonderful, but I think the saturday markets feel of the retainers &amp; market wards could work with some tweaks and with at least some degree of centralisation of market selling/buying - ie instead of having to check every individual retainer, instead the retainers act as go-betweens between you and the relevant NPC stall holder. Also I think the trade system could be improved upon and if so could prove very popular. The bartering the trade system could encourage would very much work on the 'one man's trash is another's treasure' philosophy, instead of having to rely on coinage/gil as a trading currency. <br /> <br />I would also like to see a bank deposit box system somewhat similar to WoW where the player pays gil for storage space. What can I say - I'm a hoarder. Everything will be useful at some point, even if it isn't right now ^^.</div>
